cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB. 

This paper deals with natural language generation from structured data, which is a common topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of Wikidata as a source of structured data suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and knowledge representation (cs.AI). The proposed neural network architecture with copy actions is a type of sequence-to-sequence model, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation of the approach against baselines involves comparing the generated summaries to existing data, which is a task commonly found in database research (cs.DB).
